hnical analysis in the appreciation of Beethoven, Debussy, Schoenberg, and Stravinsky.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aMusic. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Composers & Musicians.2bisacsh1 aToorn, Pieter C. van den, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052020116340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091644940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520916449423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520916449/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles